headline.main: MOSCOW PARLEY PLEDGES HUGE AID; Talks Ended Speedily as U.S. and Britain Agree to Supply Almost All Soviet Asks MOSCOW PARLEY PLEDGES HUGE AID

lead_paragraph: MOSCOW, Thursday, Oct. 2 -- The United States and Great Britain agreed to fill virtually every Soviet need for war supplies in exchange for "large quantities" of Russian raw materials at the concluding session last night of the three-power conference.
abstract: closing session; Commissar Molotoff s; Harriman and Beaverbrook issue joint statement; USSR issues communique; texts; Stalin praised in both; L Cadbury, Brit mission member, comments on difficulties
